/*
Multi-Agent Research Assistant — showcase of every orchestration pattern

  ┌──────────┐  POST /api/research  ┌────────────────┐
  │ Browser  │ ───────────────────► │ Research Topic │  (coordinator)
  │  (page)  │ ◄─────────────────── │     Agent      │
  └──────────┘       report          └───────┬────────┘
                                             │
                           ┌─────────────────┼──────────────────┐
                           ▼                 ▼                  ▼
                    ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────┐
                    │ Research All │  │ Polished Rpt │   │  Quality     │
                    │  (for each)  │  │ (repeat      │   │   Critic     │
                    └──────┬───────┘  │  until...)   │   └──────────────┘
                           │          └──────────────┘
                           ▼
                    ┌──────────────┐
                    │  Researcher  │  (helper — answers one question)
                    └──────────────┘

AGENT FLOW:

  Research Topic [skill: Report Style]
    │
    ├─ wraps topic into a 1-item list
    │
    ├─> Research All [dynamic fan-out]
    │     │
    │     └─ for each question: call Researcher ─> append to findings
    │
    └─> Polished Report [iterative refinement]
          │
          └─ repeat until score > 7, max 2 times:
               ├─ improve the draft
               └─ call Quality Critic ─> score

Five orchestration patterns in one file:
  1. Sequential chain     — Research Topic delegates step-by-step
  2. Parallel fan-out     — Grade Answer runs two graders simultaneously
  3. Dynamic fan-out      — Research All loops a list through Researcher
  4. Iterative refinement — Polished Report loops until the critic passes
  5. Skill bundle         — Report Style shared as reusable instructions
*/

build for web and javascript backend

database is local memory

# Database

create a Reports table:
  topic, required
  report, required
  created_at, auto

# Specialists

/*
These are the helpers. Each one does a single job — answer a question,
rate a claim, check a draft. The bigger agents below (the "coordinators")
call these helpers by name. The coordinator always waits for the helper's
full answer before moving on — you never see a half-finished reply.
*/

agent 'Researcher' receives question:
  answer = ask claude 'Answer this question concisely. If the user asks for a specific length (one sentence, one paragraph, etc), match that length exactly. Otherwise keep it to 2-3 sentences.' with question
  send back answer

agent 'Fact Checker' receives claim:
  verdict = ask claude 'Rate this claim 1-10 for factual accuracy. Return just the number.' with claim
  send back verdict

agent 'Sentiment Rater' receives claim:
  tone = ask claude 'Is this answer confident, cautious, or uncertain? One word.' with claim
  send back tone

agent 'Quality Critic' receives draft:
  grade = ask claude 'Rate this report 1-10 for clarity and completeness. Return just the number.' with draft
  send back grade

# Tools

/*
Regular functions that agents can call when they need to. An agent
decides on its own when to call a tool based on the instructions it's
been given. Here, character_count tells an agent how long a piece of
text is so it can stop adding to a draft that's already too long.
*/

define function character_count(text):
  size = text's length
  return size

# Skill

/*
A skill is a bundle of writing rules AND tools that you can attach to
any agent. Write it once here; every agent that says
`uses skills: 'Report Style'` gets the rules AND the tool.
No copy-paste across agents.
*/

skill 'Report Style':
  has tool: character_count
  instructions:
    Use short paragraphs.
    Lead with the answer, follow with the reasoning.
    Never say 'As an AI'.
    Call character_count on your draft. Keep the report under 1500 characters.

# Coordinators

/*
Pattern 2 — Run two helpers at the same time. This agent wants both an
accuracy score AND a tone check for the same claim. Neither depends on
the other, so `do these at the same time` runs both in parallel and
waits for both to finish before continuing.
*/
agent 'Grade Answer' receives claim:
  do these at the same time:
    accuracy = call 'Fact Checker' with claim
    tone = call 'Sentiment Rater' with claim
  create grade:
    accuracy is accuracy
    tone is tone
  send back grade

/*
Pattern 3 — Run a helper once per item in a list. The caller hands in
any number of questions. For each one, this agent asks the Researcher
helper, then adds that answer to a running list. Returns the list.
*/
agent 'Research All' receives questions:
  findings is an empty list
  for each question in questions:
    answer = call 'Researcher' with question
    add answer to findings
  send back findings

/*
Pattern 4 — Keep improving a draft until a critic says it's good enough.
This agent writes a first draft, then asks the Quality Critic for a
score. If the score is low, it rewrites and asks again. It tries up to
two rewrites — if the score is still low after that, it gives up and
returns the best draft so far. The cap keeps the agent from retrying
forever when it can't improve the draft any further.
*/
agent 'Polished Report' receives findings:
  uses skills: 'Report Style'
  draft = ask claude 'Synthesize these research findings into a single concise report on the topic. Lead with the main answer in the first sentence. Use short paragraphs. STRICT LIMIT: keep the report to roughly 1200 characters — prefer a crisp summary over exhaustive detail. Return ONLY the report prose itself — do NOT include character counts, notes about length, or any meta-commentary.' with findings
  grade = 0
  repeat until grade is greater than 7, max 1 times:
    draft = ask claude 'Tighten this report — keep the core answer, cut padding. STRICT LIMIT: roughly 1200 characters. Return ONLY the tightened report prose, no meta-commentary.' with draft
    grade = call 'Quality Critic' with draft
  send back draft

/*
Pattern 1 — Do these things in order, one after the other. This is the
top-level agent that kicks off the whole research. It puts the user's
topic into a one-item list, hands it to Research All to gather answers,
then hands those answers to Polished Report for the final write-up.
*/
agent 'Research Topic' receives topic:
  uses skills: 'Report Style'
  question_list is an empty list
  add 'Give a short, focused explanation of: ' + topic to question_list
  add 'What are the main ideas or components of: ' + topic to question_list
  add 'Why does ' + topic + ' matter?' to question_list
  findings = call 'Research All' with question_list
  final_report = call 'Polished Report' with findings
  send back final_report

# Endpoints

allow server to accept requests from frontend

when user sends request to /api/research:
  final_report = call 'Research Topic' with request's topic
  saved = save request as new Report with report is final_report
  send back saved

when user requests data from /api/reports:
  all_reports = get all Reports
  send back all_reports

# Frontend

page 'Multi-Agent Research':
  on page load get reports from '/api/reports'
  heading 'Research Assistant'
  text 'Enter a topic. The coordinator dispatches a specialist to research it, loops a critic to refine the final report, and shows the polished answer below.'
  'Topic' is a text input saved as a topic
  button 'Research':
    send topic as a new request to '/api/research'
    get reports from '/api/reports'
    topic is ''
  display reports as table showing topic, report, created_at
